Should probably be skipped for `BerkeleyDatabase`, but should have a test for `Files()`, e.g.:

<details>

<summary>

#### Maybe something like https://github.com/davidgumberg/bitcoin/commit/1428104fe9c805554e17a1a177214033b8a02a93
 
 </summary>

```cpp
#ifdef USE_SQLITE
BOOST_AUTO_TEST_CASE(sqlite_db_files)
{
    DatabaseOptions options;
    DatabaseStatus status;
    bilingual_str error;
    std::unique_ptr<SQLiteDatabase> sqldb = MakeSQLiteDatabase(m_path_root / "sqlite", options, status, error);

    auto res = sqlite3_db_filename(sqldb->m_db, "main");
    LogInfo("%s", res);
    BOOST_CHECK(1 == 1);
}
#endif
```
